Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

In a
#small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{3/4%cup}, 1 1/4 cups water (2 1/4 cups for 4), and @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Trim and halve @Zucchini{1} lengthwise; cut crosswise into 1/4-inch-thick half-moons. Trim @Green Beans{6%ounce} if necessary.

> TIP: If you added any other items to your meal (apps, sides, and/or dessert), you can get started on them now!

== Roasted Green Beans and Zucchini ==

Toss zucchini on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tbsp}, @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{}.

Toss green beans on empty side of baking sheet with a drizzle of oil, @salt{pinch}, and pepper.

> For 4 servings, toss zucchini and green beans on two separate sheets.

Roast on top rack until veggies are browned and tender, ~{10-12%minutes}.

> For 4, roast on top and middle racks, swapping rack positions halfway through.

== Broccoli ==

Place @Broccoli{8%ounce}(cut into bite-size pieces if necessary) in a large #microwave-safe bowl{}; cover tightly with #plastic wrap{} and poke a few holes in wrap. Microwave until broccoli is tender, ~{3-4%minutes}. Carefully uncover (watch out for steam!) and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Tangy Slaw ==

While veggies roast, in a #medium bowl{}, toss together @Cabbage & Carrots{4%ounce}, half the @Rice Wine Vinegar{5%tsp}, @Sugar{1%tsp}, and @salt{pinch} until combined (all the vinegar and 2 tsp sugar for 4 servings). Refrigerate until ready to serve.

== Sweet Chili Chicken ==

Open package of @Diced Chicken Thighs{10%ounce} and drain off any excess liquid.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook, undisturbed, until browned, ~{2%minutes}. Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until chicken is cooked through, ~{2-4%minutes} more.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Stir in @Sweet Soy Glaze{4%tbsp}, half the @Sweet Thai Chili Sauce{2%ounce}, and 1/4 cup water (1/2 cup for 4 servings); cook until sauce has reduced and chicken is coated, ~{30-60%seconds}.

== Firecracker Sauce ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, remaining chili sauce, and as much @Sriracha Sauce{2%tsp} as you like (we used 1⁄2 tsp; 1 tsp for 4 servings).

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @Butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings).

Serve rice, zucchini, green beans, slaw, chicken, firecracker sauce, @Crispy Fried Onions{1}, and any remaining Sriracha family style and let everyone build their own bowls.

> Serve broccoli alongside chicken and rice bar.